A-Bit-Bigger-WM is a Window Manager based on TinyWM written to add useful functionality like customisable keybinds

Files:
	Makefile : highly advanced build system

	keybinds/ : Keybind Customisation Files
		keybinds/keybinds.h          : Main Keybinds File
		keybinds/keybind_internal.h  : Keybind Internal File
		keybinds/keybind_wrapppers.c : File For Defining 0-Arg Wrappers
	src/ : Main Source Code Files
		src/main.c : Main Logic File
	include/ : Libraries Used
		include/shared.h : A Small Library With Useful Function Definitions Including A Small Process Runner

Configuration:
	For Key Combinations Or Mouse Combinations Edit Either The keybinds or mouse_events Structs in keybinds/keybinds.h Accordingly

Defaults:
	The Default Events Are:
		Alt+F1     : Move The Selected Window Up
		Alt+Mouse1 : Move The Selected Window
		Alt+Mouse3 : Resize The Selected Window
